🔹 1. System Design
1.The program is designed using a modular approach
2.Divided into three main modules:
3.Contacts (Linked List)
4.Messages (Queue)
5.Call History (Stack)

🔹 2. Data Structure Implementation
-->📞 Contacts → Linked List
1.Dynamic memory allocation using new
2.Each contact stored as a node
3.Allows flexible addition of contacts
-->💬 Messages → Queue (FIFO)
1.Implemented using array
2.Messages are stored in order
3.First message is deleted first
-->📱 Call History → Stack (LIFO)
1.Implemented using array
2.Last call stored at top
3.Last call deleted first

🔹 3. User Interaction
1.Menu-driven system
2.User selects options (1–9)
3.Input taken using cin and getline()

🔹 4. Processing Logic
Uses:
1.Functions for each operation
2.Switch-case for menu control
3.Conditions (if-else) for validations

🔹 5. Memory Management
1.Contacts use dynamic memory
2.freeContacts() function deletes allocated memory
3.Prevents memory leakage

🔹 6. Program Flow
1.Start program
2.Display menu
3.Read user choice
4.Call respective function
5.Perform operation
6.Display result
7.Repeat until Exit
8.Free memory and stop
